1. DEFINITIONS

   "Specification" means the USS grammar rules, EBNF definition, token format
   conventions, case-based taxonomy, and encoding methodology described in the
   accompanying project report.

   "Database" means any curated collection of USS-encoded equations, symbols,
   registries, or dependency graphs derived from this project.

   "Implementation" means any software, parser, API, or tool that implements
   the USS Specification.

2. SPECIFICATION USAGE (Permissive)

   The USS Specification may be referenced, discussed, and used for academic
   research, educational purposes, and standardization proposals without charge,
   provided that:

   a) Proper attribution is given to Tarek Mohammed Nasser as the original author.
   b) Any derivative specification clearly states it is based on USS.
   c) The Specification is not misrepresented as an open standard or public domain.

3. DATABASE & REGISTRY USAGE (Restricted)

   The USS Symbol Registry, Core Equation Database, and any curated content
   derived from this project are proprietary. Use, reproduction, distribution,
   or incorporation into commercial products requires explicit written permission
   from the copyright holder.

   Academic institutions may request limited access for non-commercial research
   subject to a signed academic use agreement.

4. IMPLEMENTATION LICENSING

   Software implementations of the USS Specification are subject to separate
   licensing terms. Contact the author for:

   a) Open-source implementation licenses (academic/non-profit)
   b) Commercial implementation licenses
   c) Enterprise integration licenses

5. NO WARRANTY

   THE SPECIFICATION AND ALL ASSOCIATED MATERIALS ARE PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT
   WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE
   WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, AND
   NON-INFRINGEMENT.

6. ATTRIBUTION

   All publications, presentations, or implementations referencing USS must include
   the following citation:

   Tarek Mohammed Nasser. "Unified Symbol System (USS) for All Sciences:
   Project Overview and Implementation Strategy." v1.1, 2026.

7. GOVERNANCE

   The symbol registry governance protocol will be established upon completion
   of Phase 0 (Months 1–2). Until then, all registry decisions are made by the
   copyright holder.

